Reasoning: The paper deals with visual relation detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the connection between computer vision and natural language, indicating that it may also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The proposed model uses relational representation learning and convolutional object detection networks, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on large-scale datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
